==Latin==

===Adverb===
'''iam'''
# [[already]]
# [[now]]
# [[anymore]]

====Usage note====
"Iam" means, generally, "at some point previous" or "since some point previous."  In English, "already," the most common translation, is used only to emphasize that this point might have been expected to be later, whereas "now" is used to emphasize that the the statement was once false.  "Iam" is used to express either.  (Likewise, the most common Latin word for "now," "[[nunc]]," means only the literal present moment.)  Also, where "iam" means "now," it is often used in negative sentences, in which the most common English construction uses "anymore."

